# Copy to .env.local (or set in Cloudflare Pages → Environment variables).
# Web OAuth client ID; enable Drive API; OAuth scope: drive.file
# https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#
# OAuth consent screen — must match visible branding on https://pitch.5dlabs.ai/
# App name: use "5D Labs" or "5D Labs — Investor Deck" (do not use internal codenames like "PitchDeck").
# Home page lists Privacy + Terms in the footer; policy URL for Google:
#   https://pitch.5dlabs.ai/privacy/
#   https://pitch.5dlabs.ai/terms/
#
# --- 1Password ---
# The JSON from Google Cloud includes a client_secret. The static Next.js app does NOT use
# the secret in the browser (only NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID). Keep the secret in 1Password:
#
# 1) Create an item (e.g. "Google OAuth — Pitch Deck") in your vault.
# 2) Add text field "client_id" and password field "client_secret", OR attach the JSON as a file.
# 3) Copy google-oauth.env.op.defaults → local.env.op and set op://Vault/Item/field paths.
# 4) Run: bash scripts/ensure-google-oauth-env.sh   (first time)
#    Then: op run --env-file=local.env.op -- npm run dev
#
# If the client_secret was shared or committed anywhere, rotate it in Google Cloud Console
# (Credentials → your OAuth client → Reset secret) and update 1Password.
#
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
